CNCP v1 23993
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#13528: `selected` attribute on `select option` won't get added when the `select` is using `:value` instead of `v-model`",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:16:16.938581+00:00",
  "text": "`selected` attribute on `select option` won't get added when the `select` is using `:value` instead of `v-model`\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.17\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#__SSR__\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nSwitch line 8 and 9 to see the different result in SSR tab.\n\n### What is expected?\n\n`<select :value=\"value\">` should result in the same under SSR like `<select v-model=\"value\">`\n```js\nfunction ssrRender(_ctx, _push, _parent, _attrs, $props, $setup, $data, $options) {\n  _push(`<select${\n    _ssrRenderAttrs(_attrs)\n  }><!-- <select :value=\"value\"> --><option value=\"test\"${\n    (_ssrIncludeBooleanAttr((Array.isArray($setup.value))\n      ? _ssrLooseContain($setup.value, \"test\")\n      : _ssrLooseEqual($setup.value, \"test\"))) ? \" selected\" : \"\"\n  }>test option</option></select>`)\n}\n```\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\n```js\nfunction ssrRender(_ctx, _push, _parent, _attrs, $props, $setup, $data, $options) {\n  _push(`<!--[--><!-- <select v-model=\"value\"> --><select${_ssrRenderAttrs(_mergeProps({ value: $setup.value }, _attrs))}><option value=\"test\">test option</option></select><!--]-->`)\n}\n```\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nIf `v-model` still remains syntax sugar in vue3 like in vue2 <sup>[[1]][[2]]</sup>, there should be no different.\n\n  [1]: https://v2.vuejs.org/v2/guide/forms\n  [2]: https://github.com/vuejs/babel-plugin-jsx/issues/636#issuecomment-1657199973",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: ssr",
    "has workaround",
    ":hammer: p3-minor-bug"
  ],
